"Santos A.P., Ferreira L., Maroco J., Oliveira M.M.","Abiotic stress and induced DNA hypomethylation cause interphase chromatin structural changes in rice rDNA loci",2011,"Cytogenetic and Genome Research","132","4",,"297","303",,,10.1159/000322287,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-79951568936&partnerID=40&md5=82043bb26e707cffa27e82c2fc4bb4a1","Genomics of Plant Stress Laboratory, Instituto de Tecnologia Química e Biológica, Quinta Do Marquês, Av. da República, PT-2780-157 Oeiras, Portugal; UIPES, ISPA-Instituto Universitário, Lisbon, Portugal","Santos, A.P., Genomics of Plant Stress Laboratory, Instituto de Tecnologia Química e Biológica, Quinta Do Marquês, Av. da República, PT-2780-157 Oeiras, Portugal; Ferreira, L., Genomics of Plant Stress Laboratory, Instituto de Tecnologia Química e Biológica, Quinta Do Marquês, Av. da República, PT-2780-157 Oeiras, Portugal; Maroco, J., UIPES, ISPA-Instituto Universitário, Lisbon, Portugal; Oliveira, M.M., Genomics of Plant Stress Laboratory, Instituto de Tecnologia Química e Biológica, Quinta Do Marquês, Av. da República, PT-2780-157 Oeiras, Portugal","Global climate change, i.e. higher and more variable temperatures, and a gain in soil salinity are increasing plant stress with direct consequences on crop yield and quality levels. Rice productivity is strongly affected by abiotic stress conditions. The regulation of chromatin structure in response to environmental stress is poorly understood. We investigated the interphase chromatin organization from rice plants in non-stress versus stress conditions. We have used a cytogenetic approach, based on fluorescence in situ hybridization (FISH) with 45S, 5S rDNA and centromeric probes on rice tissue sections. The abiotic stress conditions included cold, heat and mild salinity and were applied during seed germination. In contrast to cold, saline and heat stresses caused extensive decondensation of 45S rDNA chromatin and also an increase in the distance between the 2 homologous 5S rDNA loci. 5-Azacytidine (5-AC), a DNA hypomethylating drug, greatly increased 45S rDNA chromatin decondensation and interestingly was able to induce polarization of centromeres in rice interphase nuclei. The abiotic stresses tested did not perturb the spatial position of centromeres, typically with circular arrangement around the nucleolus. The results suggest a role for chromatin plasticity in a world of climate changes. Copyright © 2011 S. Karger AG, Basel.","5-Azacytidine; Abiotic stress; Chromatin organization; rDNA; Rice","azacitidine; DNA 5S; ribosome DNA; abiotic stress; article; centromere; chromatin condensation; chromatin structure; chromosome analysis; cold stress; controlled study; DNA methylation; fluorescence in situ hybridization; germination; heat stress; interphase; nonhuman; nucleolus; priority journal; rice; salt stress; tissue section; Azacitidine; Centromere; Chromatin; Chromosomes, Plant; Cold Temperature; DNA Methylation; DNA, Ribosomal; Hot Temperature; In Situ Hybridization, Fluorescence; Interphase; Oryza sativa; Salinity; Stress, Physiological",,"azacitidine, 320-67-2, 52934-49-3; Azacitidine, 320-67-2; Chromatin; DNA, Ribosomal",,,,"Abranches, R., Beven, A.F., Aragon-Alcaide, L., Shaw, P.J., Transcription sites are not correlated with chromosome territories in wheat nuclei (1998) Journal of Cell Biology, 143 (1), pp. 5-12. , DOI 10.1083/jcb.143.1.5; Abranches, R., Santos, A.P., Wegel, E., Williams, S., Castilho, A., Christou, P., Shaw, P., Stoger, E., Widely separated multiple transgene integration sites in wheat chromosomes are brought together at interphase (2000) Plant Journal, 24 (6), pp. 713-723. , DOI 10.1046/j.1365-313X.2000.00908.x; Amasino, R., Vernalization, competence, and the epigenetic memory of winter (2004) Plant Cell, 16 (10), pp. 2553-2559. , DOI 10.1105/tpc.104.161070; Arnholdt-Schmitt, B., Stress-induced cell reprogramming. A role for global genome regulation? (2004) Plant Physiology, 136 (1), pp. 2579-2